{"key":"processedPost-6348906","value":{"id":6348906,"first":6345322,"last":6351006,"when":1165629320,"utime":"12/09/06 03:55 AM","content":"Don't fill a spawn bag more than half full.  Be sure to leave plenty of room in the top for a plenum of air.  You want to make sure the top of the bag is inflated, almost like a balloon before you seal it.<br /><br />A very important factor to remember, the larger the spawn bag, the drier you make your grains.  For very large bags, after the first shake, I lay the bag flat on it's back with the grains spread out, and the filter patch on top.  For smaller bags, they can stay sitting upright.<br />RR","title":"Re: ok got my spawn bags and spores now have q's","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}